In article <1993Oct2.124024.24965@uwasa.fi>
hensel@garbo.uwasa.fi (Mike Hensel) writes:
 
>i intend to develop a program for ms-dos that will encrypt hard disks
>on a sector level. for this, i need a fast and strong cipher, that
>allows random access to the encrypted data stream. this means, i need
>to be able to decrypt only a small portion of the stream, without reading
>all the previous data. likewise, i need to be able to change small portion
>of data, without having to re-encrypt nothing more but the data that is
>being changed. any suggestions?
 
   This general topic came up a while back.  I suggested encrypting each
sector with IDEA in CBC-mode, but generating a new IV for each sector
by encrypting a the sector number + some constant with the secret key.
Bitnote me, and I'll explain this more completely, if you're interested.
 
>regards,
>Mike Hensel
 
